15/04/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- A school bus collided with a truck in central Turkey on Saturday (14 April), killing 33 people and injuring 35 others.
Most of the victims were students from a primary school in Izmir who were headed to Cappadocia.
Police sources say the driver of the bus, who was among the victims, had tried to pass another vehicle when the collision took place.
The bus reportedly was carrying 20 people more than its capacity.
(Cihan, Focus, Deutsche Welle - 15/04/07;
Darik, Reuters - 14/04/07)
